FRONT END

Objectives:
1. Understand differenc between Front End and Back End code
2. Understand roles of HTML, CSS, and JS

Front End vs Back End

1. Front End if stuff users sees and interacts with: HTML, CSS, and JS
2. Back End is everything else: many choices - python, databases (postgresql, mysql), apache, etc
3. Restaurant analogy - The backend is everything happening in kitchen; the front end is what is presented on a plate. 

Static Webpage - always the same
Dynamic webpage - changes depending on certain information. Usually deals with databases. 

HTML:
-HyperText Markup Language
-Defines structure of webpage:
	-Put image here
	-Put a form here
-The "nouns" of a webpage
	-the skeleton of webpage
-Must have HTML

CSS:
-Cascading Style Sheet
-Defines style of HTML
	-"Make all text purple"
	-"Give first image a yellow border"
-The "adjectives" of a web page

JavaScript
-Adds logic and interactivity to a page
	-"Do some math"
	-"Change color when user clicks"
	-"Load new data from twitter"
-The actions or "verbs" of a webpage
